      "role": "user",
      "content": "well if the garlic isn't strong enough then what about the vitamin k? if i drink a lot of green juice every single day it would basically be like a constant dose of natural stuff in my system. i've heard people say you can use diet to balance out your blood thinners. if i was really strict about it, could i eventually taper off the warfarin and just rely on my diet and the supplements to keep everything stable? maybe just give me an idea of how i'd make that transition.",
